#. <section class="sutta" id="mn139"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn139:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 139"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 139"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn139:0.2"
msgid "Araṇavibhaṅgasutta"
msgstr "The Analysis of Non-Conflict"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.230"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn139:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn139:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn139:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn139:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn139:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:2.1"
msgid "“araṇavibhaṅgaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi."
msgstr "“Mendicants, I shall teach you the analysis of non-conflict."

msgctxt "mn139:2.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn139:2.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn139:2.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Na kāmasukhamanuyuñjeyya hīnaṃ gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ "
"anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na ca attakilamathānuyogamanuyuñjeyya dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ "
"anatthasaṃhitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Don’t indulge in sensual pleasures, which are low, crude, ordinary, "
"ignoble, and pointless. And don’t indulge in self-mortification, which is "
"painful, ignoble, and pointless."

msgctxt "mn139:3.2"
msgid ""
"Ete kho, bhikkhave, ubho ante anupagamma majjhimā paṭipadā tathāgatena "
"abhisambuddhā, cakkhukaraṇī ñāṇakaraṇī upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya "
"nibbānāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"Avoiding these two extremes, the Realized One woke up by understanding the "
"middle way, which gives vision and knowledge, and leads to peace, direct "
"knowledge, awakening, and extinguishment."

msgctxt "mn139:3.3"
msgid "Ussādanañca jaññā, apasādanañca jaññā;"
msgstr "Know what it means to flatter and to rebuke."

#. VAR: apasādeyya → nāpasādeyya (bj)
msgctxt "mn139:3.4"
msgid ""
"ussādanañca ñatvā apasādanañca ñatvā nevussādeyya, na apasādeyya, dhammameva "
"deseyya."
msgstr "Knowing these, avoid them, and just teach Dhamma."

msgctxt "mn139:3.5"
msgid "Sukhavinicchayaṃ jaññā;"
msgstr "Know how to distinguish different kinds of pleasure."

msgctxt "mn139:3.6"
msgid "sukhavinicchayaṃ ñatvā ajjhattaṃ sukhamanuyuñjeyya."
msgstr "Knowing this, pursue inner bliss."

#. VAR: na khīṇaṃ → nātikhīṇaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn139:3.7"
msgid "Rahovādaṃ na bhāseyya, sammukhā na khīṇaṃ bhaṇe."
msgstr ""
"Don’t talk behind people’s backs, and don’t speak sharply in their presence."

msgctxt "mn139:3.8"
msgid "Ataramānova bhāseyya, no taramāno."
msgstr "Don’t speak hurriedly."

msgctxt "mn139:3.9"
msgid "Janapadaniruttiṃ nābhiniveseyya, samaññaṃ nātidhāveyyāti—"
msgstr "Don’t insist on local terminology and don’t override normal usage."

msgctxt "mn139:3.10"
msgid "ayamuddeso araṇavibhaṅgassa."
msgstr "This is the recitation passage for the analysis of non-conflict."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.231"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:4.1"
msgid ""
"‘Na kāmasukhamanuyuñjeyya hīnaṃ gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ "
"anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na ca attakilamathānuyogamanuyuñjeyya dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ "
"anatthasaṃhitan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Don’t indulge in sensual pleasures, which are low, crude, ordinary, "
"ignoble, and pointless. And don’t indulge in self-mortification, which is "
"painful, ignoble, and pointless.’"

msgctxt "mn139:4.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ; Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn139:4.3"
msgid ""
"Yo kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogo hīno gammo pothujjaniko anariyo "
"anatthasaṃhito, sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho; "
"micchāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""
"Pleasure linked to sensuality is low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and "
"pointless. Indulging in such happiness is a principle beset by pain, harm, "
"stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way."

msgctxt "mn139:4.4"
msgid ""
"Yo kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogaṃ ananuyogo hīnaṃ gammaṃ "
"pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto "
"anupāyāso apariḷāho; sammāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""
"Breaking off such indulgence is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and "
"fever, and it is the right way."

msgctxt "mn139:4.5"
msgid ""
"Yo attakilamathānuyogo dukkho anariyo anatthasaṃhito, sadukkho eso dhammo "
"saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho; micchāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""
"Indulging in self-mortification is painful, ignoble, and pointless. It is a "
"principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way."

msgctxt "mn139:4.6"
msgid ""
"Yo attakilamathānuyogaṃ ananuyogo dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, adukkho "
"eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho; sammāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""
"Breaking off such indulgence is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and "
"fever, and it is the right way."

msgctxt "mn139:4.7"
msgid ""
"‘Na kāmasukhamanuyuñjeyya hīnaṃ gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ "
"anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na ca attakilamathānuyogaṃ anuyuñjeyya dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ "
"anatthasaṃhitan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Don’t indulge in sensual pleasures, which are low, crude, ordinary, "
"ignoble, and pointless. And don’t indulge in self-mortification, which is "
"painful, ignoble, and pointless.’"

msgctxt "mn139:4.8"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:5.1"
msgid ""
"‘Ete kho ubho ante anupagamma majjhimā paṭipadā tathāgatena abhisambuddhā, "
"cakkhukaraṇī ñāṇakaraṇī upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya "
"saṃvattatī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Avoiding these two extremes, the Realized One woke up by understanding the "
"middle way, which gives vision and knowledge, and leads to peace, direct "
"knowledge, awakening, and extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "mn139:5.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn139:5.3"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "mn139:5.4"
msgid ""
"sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, "
"sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

msgctxt "mn139:5.5"
msgid ""
"‘Ete kho ubho ante anupagamma majjhimā paṭipadā tathāgatena abhisambuddhā, "
"cakkhukaraṇī ñāṇakaraṇī upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya "
"saṃvattatī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Avoiding these two extremes, the Realized One woke up by understanding the "
"middle way, which gives vision and knowledge, and leads to peace, direct "
"knowledge, awakening, and extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "mn139:5.6"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:6.1"
msgid "‘Ussādanañca jaññā, apasādanañca jaññā;"
msgstr "‘Know what it means to flatter and to rebuke."

msgctxt "mn139:6.2"
msgid ""
"ussādanañca ñatvā apasādanañca ñatvā nevussādeyya, na apasādeyya, dhammameva "
"deseyyā’ti—"
msgstr "Knowing these, avoid them, and just teach Dhamma.’"

msgctxt "mn139:6.3"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:7.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, ussādanā ca hoti apasādanā ca, no ca dhammadesanā?"
msgstr "And how is there flattering and rebuking without teaching Dhamma?"

msgctxt "mn139:7.2"
msgid ""
"‘Ye kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogaṃ anuyuttā hīnaṃ gammaṃ "
"pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, sabbe te sadukkhā saupaghātā "
"saupāyāsā sapariḷāhā micchāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"In speaking like this, some are rebuked: ‘Pleasure linked to sensuality is "
"low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. All those who indulge in such "
"happiness are beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and they are "
"practicing the wrong way.’"

#. VAR: vadaṃ → iti paraṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn139:7.3"
msgid "iti vadaṃ ittheke apasādeti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:7.4"
msgid ""
"‘Ye kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogaṃ ananuyuttā hīnaṃ gammaṃ "
"pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, sabbe te adukkhā anupaghātā "
"anupāyāsā apariḷāhā sammāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"In speaking like this, some are flattered: ‘Pleasure linked to sensuality is "
"low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. All those who have broken off "
"such indulgence are free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and they are "
"practicing the right way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:7.5"
msgid "iti vadaṃ ittheke ussādeti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.232"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:7.6"
msgid ""
"‘Ye attakilamathānuyogaṃ anuyuttā dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, sabbe te "
"sadukkhā saupaghātā saupāyāsā sapariḷāhā micchāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"In speaking like this, some are rebuked: ‘Indulging in self-mortification is "
"painful, ignoble, and pointless. All those who indulge in it are beset by "
"pain, harm, stress, and fever, and they are practicing the wrong way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:7.7"
msgid "iti vadaṃ ittheke apasādeti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:7.8"
msgid ""
"‘Ye attakilamathānuyogaṃ ananuyuttā dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, sabbe "
"te adukkhā anupaghātā anupāyāsā apariḷāhā sammāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"In speaking like this, some are flattered: ‘Indulging in self-mortification "
"is painful, ignoble, and pointless. All those who have broken off such "
"indulgence are free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and they are "
"practicing the right way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:7.9"
msgid "iti vadaṃ ittheke ussādeti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:7.10"
msgid ""
"‘Yesaṃ kesañci bhavasaṃyojanaṃ appahīnaṃ, sabbe te sadukkhā saupaghātā "
"saupāyāsā sapariḷāhā micchāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"In speaking like this, some are rebuked: ‘All those who have not given up "
"the fetters of rebirth are beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and they "
"are practicing the wrong way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:7.11"
msgid "iti vadaṃ ittheke apasādeti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:7.12"
msgid ""
"‘Yesaṃ kesañci bhavasaṃyojanaṃ pahīnaṃ, sabbe te adukkhā anupaghātā "
"anupāyāsā apariḷāhā sammāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"In speaking like this, some are flattered: ‘All those who have given up the "
"fetters of rebirth are free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and they are "
"practicing the right way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:7.13"
msgid "iti vadaṃ ittheke ussādeti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:7.14"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ussādanā ca hoti apasādanā ca, no ca dhammadesanā."
msgstr "That’s how there is flattering and rebuking without teaching Dhamma."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
#. VAR: dhammadesanā ca → dhammadesanāva (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn139:8.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, nevussādanā hoti na apasādanā, dhammadesanā ca?"
msgstr ""
"And how is there neither flattering nor rebuking, and just teaching Dhamma?"

msgctxt "mn139:8.2"
msgid ""
"‘Ye kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogaṃ anuyuttā hīnaṃ gammaṃ "
"pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, sabbe te sadukkhā saupaghātā "
"saupāyāsā sapariḷāhā micchāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"You don’t say: ‘Pleasure linked to sensuality is low, crude, ordinary, "
"ignoble, and pointless. All those who indulge in such happiness are beset by "
"pain, harm, stress, and fever, and they are practicing the wrong way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.3"
msgid "na evamāha."
msgstr "Rather, by saying this you just teach Dhamma:"

msgctxt "mn139:8.4"
msgid "‘Anuyogo ca kho sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"‘The indulgence is a principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and "
"it is the wrong way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.5"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:8.6"
msgid "iti vadaṃ dhammameva deseti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:8.7"
msgid ""
"‘Ye kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogaṃ ananuyuttā hīnaṃ gammaṃ "
"pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, sabbe te adukkhā anupaghātā "
"anupāyāsā apariḷāhā sammāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"You don’t say: ‘Pleasure linked to sensuality is low, crude, ordinary, "
"ignoble, and pointless. All those who have broken off such indulgence are "
"free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and they are practicing the right "
"way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.8"
msgid "na evamāha."
msgstr "Rather, by saying this you just teach Dhamma:"

msgctxt "mn139:8.9"
msgid "‘Ananuyogo ca kho adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"‘Breaking off the indulgence is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and "
"fever, and it is the right way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.10"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:8.11"
msgid "iti vadaṃ dhammameva deseti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:8.12"
msgid ""
"‘Ye attakilamathānuyogaṃ anuyuttā dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, sabbe te "
"sadukkhā saupaghātā saupāyāsā sapariḷāhā micchāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"You don’t say: ‘Indulging in self-mortification is painful, ignoble, and "
"pointless. All those who indulge in it are beset by pain, harm, stress, and "
"fever, and they are practicing the wrong way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.13"
msgid "na evamāha."
msgstr "Rather, by saying this you just teach Dhamma:"

msgctxt "mn139:8.14"
msgid "‘Anuyogo ca kho sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"‘The indulgence is a principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and "
"it is the wrong way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.15"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:8.16"
msgid "iti vadaṃ dhammameva deseti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:8.17"
msgid ""
"‘Ye attakilamathānuyogaṃ ananuyuttā dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, sabbe "
"te adukkhā anupaghātā anupāyāsā apariḷāhā sammāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"You don’t say: ‘Indulging in self-mortification is painful, ignoble, and "
"pointless. All those who have broken off such indulgence are free of pain, "
"harm, stress, and fever, and they are practicing the right way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.18"
msgid "na evamāha."
msgstr "Rather, by saying this you just teach Dhamma:"

msgctxt "mn139:8.19"
msgid "‘Ananuyogo ca kho adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"‘Breaking off the indulgence is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and "
"fever, and it is the right way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.20"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:8.21"
msgid "iti vadaṃ dhammameva deseti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.233"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:8.22"
msgid ""
"‘Yesaṃ kesañci bhavasaṃyojanaṃ appahīnaṃ, sabbe te sadukkhā saupaghātā "
"saupāyāsā sapariḷāhā micchāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"You don’t say: ‘All those who have not given up the fetters of rebirth are "
"beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and they are practicing the wrong "
"way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.23"
msgid "na evamāha."
msgstr "Rather, by saying this you just teach Dhamma:"

msgctxt "mn139:8.24"
msgid "‘Bhavasaṃyojane ca kho appahīne bhavopi appahīno hotī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘When the fetter of rebirth is not given up, rebirth is also not given up.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.25"
msgid "iti vadaṃ dhammameva deseti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:8.26"
msgid ""
"‘Yesaṃ kesañci bhavasaṃyojanaṃ pahīnaṃ, sabbe te adukkhā anupaghātā "
"anupāyāsā apariḷāhā sammāpaṭipannā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"You don’t say: ‘All those who have given up the fetters of rebirth are free "
"of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and they are practicing the right way.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.27"
msgid "na evamāha."
msgstr "Rather, by saying this you just teach Dhamma:"

msgctxt "mn139:8.28"
msgid "‘Bhavasaṃyojane ca kho pahīne bhavopi pahīno hotī’ti—"
msgstr "‘When the fetter of rebirth is given up, rebirth is also given up.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.29"
msgid "iti vadaṃ dhammameva deseti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:8.30"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, nevussādanā hoti na apasādanā, dhammadesanā ca."
msgstr ""
"That’s how there is neither flattering nor rebuking, and just teaching "
"Dhamma."

msgctxt "mn139:8.31"
msgid "‘Ussādanañca jaññā, apasādanañca jaññā;"
msgstr "‘Know what it means to flatter and to rebuke."

msgctxt "mn139:8.32"
msgid ""
"ussādanañca ñatvā apasādanañca ñatvā nevussādeyya, na apasādeyya, dhammameva "
"deseyyā’ti—"
msgstr "Knowing these, avoid them, and just teach Dhamma.’"

msgctxt "mn139:8.33"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.234"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:9.1"
msgid "‘Sukhavinicchayaṃ jaññā;"
msgstr "‘Know how to distinguish different kinds of pleasure."

msgctxt "mn139:9.2"
msgid "sukhavinicchayaṃ ñatvā ajjhattaṃ sukhamanuyuñjeyyā’ti—"
msgstr "Knowing this, pursue inner bliss.’"

msgctxt "mn139:9.3"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn139:9.4"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "mn139:9.5"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "mn139:9.6"
msgid ""
"Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā, "
msgstr ""
"Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "mn139:9.7"
msgid "sotaviññeyyā saddā …"
msgstr "Sounds known by the ear …"

msgctxt "mn139:9.8"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyā gandhā …"
msgstr "Smells known by the nose …"

msgctxt "mn139:9.9"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyā rasā …"
msgstr "Tastes known by the tongue …"

msgctxt "mn139:9.10"
msgid ""
"kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā—"
msgstr ""
"Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "mn139:9.11"
msgid "ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "mn139:9.12"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ "
"idaṃ vuccati kāmasukhaṃ mīḷhasukhaṃ puthujjanasukhaṃ anariyasukhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The pleasure and happiness that arise from these five kinds of sensual "
"stimulation is called sensual pleasure—a filthy, common, ignoble pleasure."

msgctxt "mn139:9.13"
msgid ""
"‘Na āsevitabbaṃ, na bhāvetabbaṃ, na bahulīkātabbaṃ, bhāyitabbaṃ etassa "
"sukhassā’ti—vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"Such pleasure should not be cultivated or developed, but should be feared, I "
"say."

msgctxt "mn139:9.14"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Now, take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded "
"from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which "
"has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and "
"keeping it connected."

msgctxt "mn139:9.15"
msgid ""
"Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter "
"and remain in the second absorption …"

msgctxt "mn139:9.16"
msgid "Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "mn139:9.17"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

msgctxt "mn139:9.18"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ vuccati nekkhammasukhaṃ pavivekasukhaṃ upasamasukhaṃ sambodhisukhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This is called the pleasure of renunciation, the pleasure of seclusion, the "
"pleasure of peace, the pleasure of awakening."

msgctxt "mn139:9.19"
msgid ""
"‘Āsevitabbaṃ, bhāvetabbaṃ, bahulīkātabbaṃ, na bhāyitabbaṃ etassa "
"sukhassā’ti—vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"Such pleasure should be cultivated and developed, and should not be feared, "
"I say."

msgctxt "mn139:9.20"
msgid "‘Sukhavinicchayaṃ jaññā;"
msgstr "‘Know how to distinguish different kinds of pleasure."

msgctxt "mn139:9.21"
msgid "sukhavinicchayaṃ ñatvā ajjhattaṃ sukhamanuyuñjeyyā’ti—"
msgstr "Knowing this, pursue inner bliss.’"

msgctxt "mn139:9.22"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:10.1"
msgid "‘Rahovādaṃ na bhāseyya, sammukhā na khīṇaṃ bhaṇe’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Don’t talk behind people’s backs, and don’t speak sharply in their "
"presence.’"

msgctxt "mn139:10.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said,"

msgctxt "mn139:10.3"
msgid "Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "but why did I say it?"

#. VAR: sasakkaṃ → sampattaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn139:10.4"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yaṃ jaññā rahovādaṃ abhūtaṃ atacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ "
"sasakkaṃ taṃ rahovādaṃ na bhāseyya."
msgstr ""
"When you know that what you say behind someone’s back is untrue, false, and "
"harmful, then if at all possible you should not speak."

msgctxt "mn139:10.5"
msgid ""
"Yampi jaññā rahovādaṃ bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ tassapi sikkheyya "
"avacanāya."
msgstr ""
"When you know that what you say behind someone’s back is true and correct, "
"but harmful, then you should train yourself not to speak."

msgctxt "mn139:10.6"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho jaññā rahovādaṃ bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ tatra kālaññū assa "
"tassa rahovādassa vacanāya."
msgstr ""
"When you know that what you say behind someone’s back is true, correct, and "
"beneficial, then you should know the right time to speak."

msgctxt "mn139:10.7"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yaṃ jaññā sammukhā khīṇavādaṃ abhūtaṃ atacchaṃ "
"anatthasaṃhitaṃ sasakkaṃ taṃ sammukhā khīṇavādaṃ na bhāseyya."
msgstr ""
"When you know that your sharp words in someone’s presence are untrue, false, "
"and harmful, then if at all possible you should not speak."

msgctxt "mn139:10.8"
msgid ""
"Yampi jaññā sammukhā khīṇavādaṃ bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ tassapi "
"sikkheyya avacanāya."
msgstr ""
"When you know that your sharp words in someone’s presence are true and "
"correct, but harmful, then you should train yourself not to speak."

msgctxt "mn139:10.9"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho jaññā sammukhā khīṇavādaṃ bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ tatra "
"kālaññū assa tassa sammukhā khīṇavādassa vacanāya."
msgstr ""
"When you know that your sharp words in someone’s presence are true, correct, "
"and beneficial, then you should know the right time to speak."

msgctxt "mn139:10.10"
msgid "‘Rahovādaṃ na bhāseyya, sammukhā na khīṇaṃ bhaṇe’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Don’t talk behind people’s backs, and don’t speak sharply in their "
"presence.’"

msgctxt "mn139:10.11"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:11.1"
msgid "‘Ataramānova bhāseyya no taramāno’ti—"
msgstr "‘Don’t speak hurriedly.’"

msgctxt "mn139:11.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

#. VAR: upahaññati → ūhaññati (si)
msgctxt "mn139:11.3"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, taramānassa bhāsato kāyopi kilamati, cittampi upahaññati, "
"saropi upahaññati, kaṇṭhopi āturīyati, avisaṭṭhampi hoti aviññeyyaṃ "
"taramānassa bhāsitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When speaking hurriedly, your body gets tired, your mind gets stressed, your "
"voice gets stressed, your throat gets sore, and your words become unclear "
"and hard to understand."

msgctxt "mn139:11.4"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, ataramānassa bhāsato kāyopi na kilamati, cittampi na "
"upahaññati, saropi na upahaññati, kaṇṭhopi na āturīyati, visaṭṭhampi hoti "
"viññeyyaṃ ataramānassa bhāsitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When not speaking hurriedly, your body doesn’t get tired, your mind doesn’t "
"get stressed, your voice doesn’t get stressed, your throat doesn’t get sore, "
"and your words are clear and easy to understand."

msgctxt "mn139:11.5"
msgid "‘Ataramānova bhāseyya, no taramāno’ti—"
msgstr "‘Don’t speak hurriedly.’"

msgctxt "mn139:11.6"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.235"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:12.1"
msgid "‘Janapadaniruttiṃ nābhiniveseyya, samaññaṃ nātidhāveyyā’ti—"
msgstr "‘Don’t insist on local terminology and don’t override normal usage.’"

msgctxt "mn139:12.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "mn139:12.3"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, janapadaniruttiyā ca abhiniveso hoti samaññāya ca "
"atisāro?"
msgstr "And how do you insist on local terminology and override normal usage?"

#. VAR: dhāropan’ti → harosanti (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: vittan’ti → vitthanti (bj, pts1) | piṭṭhanti (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: pisīlavan’ti → pipilanti (s1-3, km) | pisīlanti (pts1)
msgctxt "mn139:12.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, tadevekaccesu janapadesu ‘pātī’ti sañjānanti, ‘pattan’ti "
"sañjānanti, ‘vittan’ti sañjānanti, ‘sarāvan’ti sañjānanti ‘dhāropan’ti "
"sañjānanti, ‘poṇan’ti sañjānanti, ‘pisīlavan’ti sañjānanti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when in different localities the same thing is known as a ‘plate’, a "
"‘bowl’, a ‘cup’, a ‘dish’, a ‘basin’, a ‘tureen’, or a ‘porringer’."

#. VAR: parāmāsā → parāmassa (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn139:12.5"
msgid ""
"Iti yathā yathā naṃ tesu tesu janapadesu sañjānanti tathā tathā thāmasā "
"parāmāsā abhinivissa voharati:"
msgstr ""
"And however it is known in those various localities, you speak accordingly, "
"obstinately sticking to that and insisting:"

msgctxt "mn139:12.6"
msgid "‘idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññan’ti."
msgstr "‘This is the only truth, other ideas are stupid.’"

msgctxt "mn139:12.7"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, janapadaniruttiyā ca abhiniveso hoti samaññāya ca "
"atisāro."
msgstr "That’s how you insist on local terminology and override normal usage."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:12.8"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, janapadaniruttiyā ca anabhiniveso hoti samaññāya ca "
"anatisāro?"
msgstr ""
"And how do you not insist on local terminology and not override normal usage?"

msgctxt "mn139:12.9"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, tadevekaccesu janapadesu ‘pātī’ti sañjānanti, ‘pattan’ti "
"sañjānanti, ‘vittan’ti sañjānanti, ‘sarāvan’ti sañjānanti, ‘dhāropan’ti "
"sañjānanti, ‘poṇan’ti sañjānanti, ‘pisīlavan’ti sañjānanti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when in different localities the same thing is known as a ‘plate’, a "
"‘bowl’, a ‘cup’, a ‘dish’, a ‘basin’, a ‘tureen’, or a ‘porringer’."

#. VAR: idaṃ kira me → idaṃ kira te ca (mr)
msgctxt "mn139:12.10"
msgid ""
"Iti yathā yathā naṃ tesu tesu janapadesu sañjānanti ‘idaṃ kira me āyasmanto "
"sandhāya voharantī’ti tathā tathā voharati aparāmasaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And however it is known in those various localities, you speak accordingly, "
"thinking: ‘It seems that the venerables are referring to this.’"

msgctxt "mn139:12.11"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, janapadaniruttiyā ca anabhiniveso hoti, samaññāya ca "
"anatisāro."
msgstr ""
"That’s how you don’t insist on local terminology and don’t override normal "
"usage."

msgctxt "mn139:12.12"
msgid "‘Janapadaniruttiṃ nābhiniveseyya samaññaṃ nātidhāveyyā’ti—"
msgstr "‘Don’t insist on local terminology and don’t override normal usage.’"

msgctxt "mn139:12.13"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:13.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yo kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogo hīno gammo "
"pothujjaniko anariyo anatthasaṃhito, sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto "
"saupāyāso sapariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Now, mendicants, pleasure linked to sensuality is low, crude, ordinary, "
"ignoble, and pointless. Indulging in such happiness is a principle beset by "
"pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.2"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.3"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict."

msgctxt "mn139:13.4"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yo kāmapaṭisandhisukhino somanassānuyogaṃ ananuyogo hīnaṃ "
"gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto "
"anupāyāso apariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Breaking off such indulgence is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and "
"fever, and it is the right way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.5"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.6"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:13.7"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yo attakilamathānuyogo dukkho anariyo anatthasaṃhito, "
"sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Indulging in self-mortification is painful, ignoble, and pointless. It is a "
"principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.8"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.9"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict."

msgctxt "mn139:13.10"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yo attakilamathānuyogaṃ ananuyogo dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ "
"anatthasaṃhitaṃ, adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Breaking off such indulgence is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and "
"fever, and it is the right way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.11"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.12"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.236"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:13.13"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ majjhimā paṭipadā tathāgatena abhisambuddhā, "
"cakkhukaraṇī ñāṇakaraṇī upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati, "
"adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"The middle way by which the Realized One was awakened gives vision and "
"knowledge, and leads to peace, direct knowledge, awakening, and "
"extinguishment. It is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and "
"it is the right way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.14"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.15"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:13.16"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ ussādanā ca apasādanā ca no ca dhammadesanā, "
"sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Flattering and rebuking without teaching Dhamma is a principle beset by "
"pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.17"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.18"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict."

msgctxt "mn139:13.19"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yāyaṃ nevussādanā ca na apasādanā ca dhammadesanā ca, "
"adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Neither flattering nor rebuking, and just teaching Dhamma is a principle "
"free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the right way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.20"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.21"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:13.22"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ kāmasukhaṃ mīḷhasukhaṃ pothujjanasukhaṃ "
"anariyasukhaṃ, sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Sensual pleasure—a filthy, common, ignoble pleasure—is a principle beset by "
"pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.23"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.24"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict."

msgctxt "mn139:13.25"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ nekkhammasukhaṃ pavivekasukhaṃ upasamasukhaṃ "
"sambodhisukhaṃ, adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"The pleasure of renunciation, the pleasure of seclusion, the pleasure of "
"peace, the pleasure of awakening is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, "
"and fever, and it is the right way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.26"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.27"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:13.28"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ rahovādo abhūto ataccho anatthasaṃhito, sadukkho "
"eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Saying untrue, false, and harmful things behind someone’s back is a "
"principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.29"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.30"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict."

msgctxt "mn139:13.31"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ rahovādo bhūto taccho anatthasaṃhito, sadukkho eso "
"dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Saying true and correct, but harmful things behind someone’s back is a "
"principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.32"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.33"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict."

msgctxt "mn139:13.34"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ rahovādo bhūto taccho atthasaṃhito, adukkho eso "
"dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Saying true, correct, and beneficial things behind someone’s back is a "
"principle free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the right way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.35"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.36"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.237"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:13.37"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ sammukhā khīṇavādo abhūto ataccho anatthasaṃhito, "
"sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Saying untrue, false, and harmful things in someone’s presence is a "
"principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.38"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.39"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict."

msgctxt "mn139:13.40"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ sammukhā khīṇavādo bhūto taccho anatthasaṃhito, "
"sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Saying true and correct, but harmful things in someone’s presence is a "
"principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.41"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.42"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict."

msgctxt "mn139:13.43"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ sammukhā khīṇavādo bhūto taccho atthasaṃhito, "
"adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Saying true, correct, and beneficial things in someone’s presence is a "
"principle free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the right way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.44"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.45"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:13.46"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ taramānassa bhāsitaṃ, sadukkho eso dhammo "
"saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Speaking hurriedly is a principle beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, "
"and it is the wrong way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.47"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.48"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict."

msgctxt "mn139:13.49"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ ataramānassa bhāsitaṃ, adukkho eso dhammo "
"anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Speaking unhurriedly is a principle free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, "
"and it is the right way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.50"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.51"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:13.52"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ janapadaniruttiyā ca abhiniveso samaññāya ca "
"atisāro, sadukkho eso dhammo saupaghāto saupāyāso sapariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Insisting on local terminology and overriding normal usage is a principle "
"beset by pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the wrong way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.53"
msgid "micchāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.54"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo saraṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle beset by conflict."

msgctxt "mn139:13.55"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ janapadaniruttiyā ca anabhiniveso samaññāya ca "
"anatisāro, adukkho eso dhammo anupaghāto anupāyāso apariḷāho;"
msgstr ""
"Not insisting on local terminology and not overriding normal usage is a "
"principle free of pain, harm, stress, and fever, and it is the right way."

msgctxt "mn139:13.56"
msgid "sammāpaṭipadā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn139:13.57"
msgid "Tasmā eso dhammo araṇo."
msgstr "That’s why this is a principle free of conflict."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:14.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘saraṇañca dhammaṃ jānissāma, araṇañca dhammaṃ "
"jānissāma;"
msgstr ""
"So you should train like this: ‘We shall know the principles beset by "
"conflict and the principles free of conflict."

msgctxt "mn139:14.2"
msgid ""
"saraṇañca dhammaṃ ñatvā araṇañca dhammaṃ ñatvā araṇapaṭipadaṃ paṭipajjissāmā’"
"ti evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr "Knowing this, we will practice the way free of conflict.’"

msgctxt "mn139:14.3"
msgid "Subhūti ca pana, bhikkhave, kulaputto araṇapaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno”ti."
msgstr ""
"And, mendicants, Subhūti, the son of a good family, practices the way of non-"
"conflict.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "mn139:14.4"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn139:14.5"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn139:14.6"
msgid "Araṇavibhaṅgasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
